Class Summary
HarmonicStrainRT The HarmonicStrain is a class
HarmonicStrainT The HarmonicStrainT is a class to compute the strain pole figure for textured sample using the harmonic expansion approximation.
MomentPoleStress The MomentPoleStress is a class to compute the diffraction shift from the triaxial stress tensor using the moment pole method of Siegfried Matthies.
NoStrain The NoStrain is a class that implements a default (zero) strain model
NoStress The NoStress is a class that implements a default (zero) stress model
PopaBalzarHarmonicStrainModel The PopaBalzarHarmonicStrainModel is a class to compute the strain based on the model published by Popa and Balzar, J.
Sla33Constants The Sla33Constants is a class to store data for the moment pole method of Siegfried Matthies.
TriaxialStress The TriaxialStress is a class to compute the diffraction shift from the triaxial stress tensor assuming isotropic elastic constants.
VoigtReussStress The VoigtReussStress is a class to compute the diffraction shift from the stress tensor using a weighted mean between Reuss and Voigt approximation.
